description.narrative: The 17 health districts (100%) provide care for children suffering from severe acute malnutrition. The conditions for managing nutrition inputs are improved through the construction of a warehouse on the island of Anjouan and technical skills-building for 85 health workers in input management. There have been no shortages of nutritional inputs, including during the emergency response. Cooking demonstrations and local food consumption promotion activities were implemented in 47% of the health districts. | Status:Met | As-of Date:17/01/2020
